<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-20T11:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-20T11:16:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.20235/84</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-20T12:00:00-04:16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1917, 12 noon</hi></date>.
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs in Senate interpellation last night
                                confined himself to reading correspondence with Imperial German
                                Government. Thereupon the Senate, 23 to 1, voted its opinion that
                                the Argentine Government should break relations with Germany.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>